l Movie Awards]]\n| [[Siima for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu|Best Actress \u2013 Telugu]]\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/siima-awards-2019-winners-rangasthalam-kgf-yash-keerthy-suresh-tamil-telugu-malayalam-kannada-5909506/|title=SIIMA 2019 winners full list: Dhanush, Trisha, Prithviraj win big|website=[[Indian Express]]|access-date=2019-11-26|date=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[T. Subbarami Reddy|TSR]] \u2013 [[TV9 (Telugu)|TV9]] National Film Awards\n| Best Actress\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/balakrishna-nagarjuna-and-keerthy-suresh-among-tsr-tv9-film-award-winners-96844|title=Balakrishna, Nagarjuna and Keerthy Suresh among TSR-TV9 film award winners|website=The News Minute|date=2019-02-16|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[66th Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards South]]\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu|Best Actress \u2013 Telugu]]\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-for-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-37931.html|title=Nominations for the 66th Filmfare Awards (South) 2019|website=[[Filmfare]]|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/winners-of-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-38163.html|title=Winners of the 66th Filmfare Awards (South) 2019|website=[[Filmfare]]|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=7146337}}\n* {{Official website|keerthysuresh4u.com}}\n\n{{National Film Award Best Actress}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Female D\u00e9butante}}\n{{Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Suresh, Keerthy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Kendriya Vidyalaya alumni]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam television]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian child actresses]]\n[[Category:Child actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Best Actress National Film Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Indian name|Keerthy|Suresh}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Keerthy Suresh\n| image              = Keerthy Suresh at Sandakozhi 2 Press Meet.png\n| caption            = Keerthy at Press Meet\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1992|10|17|df=y}}<ref name=\"indianexpress\">{{cite news|title=Happy Birthday Keerthy Suresh|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/keerthy-suresh-thaanaa-serndha-koottam-suriya-nex-film-heroine-3087223|accessdate=17 October 2016|newspaper=Indian Express India|date=17 October 2016|quote=The actor, who turned 24 on Monday, is the new favourite of Kollywood filmmakers.}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kerala]], India<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://highlightsindia.com/keerthy-suresh-early-life-and-personal-details-career-and-net-worth/ |title = Keerthy Suresh-Early Life and Personal Details, Career and Net Worth|date = 14 February 2018}}</ref>\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years active       = 2000\u20132005<br>2013\u2013present\n| parents             = {{ubl|G. Suresh Kumar|[[Menaka (actress)|Menaka]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Keerthy Suresh''' (born 17 October 1992) is an Indian film actress who appears predominantly in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Malayalam]] films. She won the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] for portraying actress [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]] in the biopic ''[[Mahanati]]'' (2018).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/malayalam/news/2014/characters-scope-to-perform-excites-me-says-keerthi-menaka-145418.html|title=Characters Which Has Scope To Perform Excites Me, Says Keerthi Menaka|work=www.filmibeat.com|accessdate=18 November 2014|date=13 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nKeerthy is the daughter of producer Suresh Kumar and actress [[Menaka (actress)|Menaka]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2013/may/13/Menaka-was-treated-like-a-queen-476820.html|title=Menaka was treated like a queen|publisher=|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref> Keerthy began acting as a child actress in the early 2000s and returned to films after studying fashion design. She had her first lead role in the 2013 [[Malayalam]] film ''[[Geethaanjali]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/siima-2014-malayalam-drishyam-gets-best-film-award-dileep-bags-best-actor-award-winners-list-609100|title=SIIMA 2014 Malayalam: 'Drishyam' Gets Best Film Award; Dileep Bags Best Actor Award &#91;Winners' List&#93;|date=15 September 2014}}</ref> She went on to star in films  such as ''[[Ring Master]]'' (2014), ''[[Idhu Enna Maayam]]'' (2015), ''[[Rajini Murugan]]'' (2016), ''[[Remo_(film)]]'' (2016), ''[[Nenu Sailaja]]'' (2016), ''[[Bairavaa]]'' (2017), ''[[Nenu Local]]'' (2017), ''[[Thaana Serndha Kootam]]'' (2018), ''[[Mahanati]]'' (2018), ''[[Sandakozhi 2]]'' (2018) and ''[[Sarkar (2018 film)|Sarkar]]'' (2018).\n\n==Early life==\nKeerthy was born to [[Malayalam]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eenadu.net/magazines/sunday-magazine/sunday-magazineinner.aspx?catfullstory=10448|title=\u0c38\u0c3f\u0c28\u0c3f\u0c2e\u0c3e \u0c15\u0c37\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c3e\u0c32\u0c47\u0c35\u0c40 \u0c32\u0c47\u0c35\u0c41...!|website=www.eenadu.net|access-date=5 February 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217081956/http://www.eenadu.net/magazines/sunday-magazine/sunday-magazineinner.aspx?catfullstory=10448|archivedate=17 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> film producer and director Suresh Kumar and [[Tamils|Tamil]] actress [[Menaka (actress)|Menaka]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/Menaka-was-treated-like-a-queen/2013/05/13/article1587175.ece|title=Menaka was treated like a queen|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://malayalam.oneindia.in/movies/news/want-to-play-memorable-roles-like-mom-keerthy-20140613141152-122280.html|title=Want to play memorable roles like mom|work=malayalam.filmibeat.com|accessdate=18 November 2014|date=13 June 2014}}</ref> She has an elder sister Revathy Suresh. Until class four, Keerthy did her schooling in [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref name=NIE>{{cite news|last1=Gupta|first1=Rinku|title=Mayas Role Is Very Close to My Heart|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Mayas-Role-Is-Very-Close-to-My-Heart/2015/04/07/article2750813.ece|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=7 April 2015|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref> She then studied in [[Kendriya Vidyalaya]], [[Pattom]], [[Thiruvananthapuram]] before coming back to Chennai to join the [[Pearl Academy]], where she completed her degree in [[fashion design]].<ref name=\"One for the family\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/one-for-the-family/article4951420.ece|title=One for the family|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=18 November 2014|date=25 July 2013|last1=Sathyendran|first1=Nita}}</ref> She also spent time on an exchange program in [[Scotland]] for four months, before completing a two-month internship in London. Despite making a career in acting, she has stated that she was also \"seriously considering a career in designing\".<ref name=\"Menaka was treated like a queen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/Menaka-was-treated-like-a-queen/2013/05/13/article1587175.ece|title=Menaka was treated like a queen|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=StarsFact|title=Keerthy Suresh| work=Keerthy Suresh Height, Weight, Age, Affairs, Wiki & Facts|date=10 November 2016|url=https://starsfact.com/keerthy-suresh/|accessdate=13 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn the early 2000s, Keerthy worked as a child actress in a few of her father's productions, such as ''[[Pilots (film)|Pilots]]'' (2000), ''[[Achaneyanenikkishtam]]'' (2001) and ''[[Kuberan (2002 film)|Kuberan]]'' (2002) and some television serials.<ref name=\"One for the family\"/> 11 years after ''Kuberan'', she made her debut as a lead actress in [[Priyadarshan]]'s horror film ''[[Geethaanjali]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nowrunning.com/nishan-to-romance-keerthi/74495/story.htm|title=Nishan to romance Keerthi|date=15 July 2013|work=Nowrunning|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> in which she had a [[dual role]]. She was still studying during that time and shot for ''Geethanjali'' during her semester break.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/A-star-is-born/2013/11/14/article1875959.ece|title=A star is born|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> Reviews on the film and her performance were mixed, with Sify writing that she \"does put in some effort but makes only a limited impression in a double role\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/geethanjali-review-malayalam-15043242.html|title=Movie Review : Geethanjali|work=Sify|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> while Rediff wrote that she \"has got a plum role but whether she impresses with her acting prowess is another matter\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-geethanjali-disappoints/20131115.htm |title=Review: Geethanjali disappoints |date=15 November 2013 |work=Rediff |accessdate=18 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129045722/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-geethanjali-disappoints/20131115.htm |archivedate=29 November 2014 |df= }}</ref> In 2014, Keerthy had her next release ''[[Ring Master]]'', directed by Rafi of [[Rafi Mecartin]] duo, in which she shared screen space with [[Dileep (actor)|Dileep]]. She played a blind girl,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Playing-a-blind-girl-is-not-an-easy-task-Keerthy-Suresh/articleshow/33651802.cms|title= Playing a blind girl is not an easy task: Keerthy Suresh|work=The Times of India|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> which she said was much more challenging than her double role in ''Geethanjali''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140412/entertainment-mollywood/article/keerthy-suresh-%E2%80%98blind%E2%80%99-date|title=Keerthy Suresh on a 'blind' date|work=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> The film was a commercial success,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/six-months-six-months-malayalam-news-109844|title=Six months, six months|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/Screening-the-Past/2014/07/01/article2308439.ece|title=Screening the Past|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> being termed a \"super hit\" by [[Sify]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=15057846&cid=14625530|title=Kerala Box-Office April 10 to June 15 Summer Hits|publisher=Sify|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Keerthy accepted her first projects outside of Malayalam and signed on to appear in several Tamil film projects simultaneously. Her first film release was [[A. L. Vijay]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Idhu Enna Maayam]]'' (2015), opposite [[Vikram Prabhu]], though the film did not perform well at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/The-shooting-of-my-first-Tamil-film-is-going-on-Keerthy-Suresh/articleshow/44847371.cms|title=The shooting of my first Tamil film is going on: Keerthy Suresh|work=The Times of India|date=17 October 2014}}</ref> Her busy schedule throughout 2015 meant that she had to opt out of films which she had already started working on, including [[N. Krishna|Krishna]]'s ''[[Maane Thaene Paeye]]'' and Deekay's ''[[Kavalai Vendam]]'', in order to accommodate bigger projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Keerthi-Suresh-is-Aaris-pair-in-Krishnas-rom-com/articleshow/41005433.cms|title=Keerthi Suresh is Aari's pair in Krishna's rom-com|work=The Times of India|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> She consequently worked on two films with [[Sivakarthikeyan]] in quick succession, ''[[Rajini Murugan]]'' and ''[[Remo (film)|Remo]]'', while also playing the lead role in [[Prabhu Solomon]]'s ''[[Thodari]]'', alongside [[Dhanush]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Anushka-Shetty-wishes-Keerthy-Suresh-luck-in-Kwood/articleshow/44917200.cms|title=Anushka Shetty wishes Keerthy Suresh luck in K'wood|work=The Times of India|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> Her Telugu debut was the 2016 film [[Nenu Sailaja]] with actor [[Ram Pothineni]]. In January 2017, Keerthy appeared in ''[[Bairavaa]]'', opposite actor [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and directed by Bharathan.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/bairavaa-bhairava-3-weeks-box-office-collection-vijays-film-earns-around-rs-110-crore-22-days-714810 | title=Bairavaa (Bhairava) 3 weeks box office collection: Vijay's film earns around Rs 110 crore in 22 days | accessdate=15 February 2017 | work=IB Times | date=4 February 2017}}</ref> She also appeared in Tamil film ''[[Paambhu Sattai]]'' and Telugu film ''[[Nenu Local]]'' in 2017.\n\nIn early 2018, she appeared in ''[[Agnyaathavaasi]]'' and ''[[Thaana Serndha Kootam]]''. She also acted in [[Nag Ashwin]]'s Telugu-Tamil bilingual epic ''[[Mahanati]]'' where she portrayed the late southern actress [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]] and for which her performance has received critical acclaim.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/mahanati-actor-keerthy-suresh-on-playing-savirtri-im-glad-i-convinced-her-daughter-with-my-portrayal-4465101.html|title=Mahanati actor Keerthy Suresh on playing Savirtri: I'm glad I convinced her daughter with my portrayal- Entertainment News, Firstpost|publisher=|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref> Her recently released movies include ''[[Saamy 2]]'', The Sequel of ''[[Saamy]]'', opposite [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]], ''[[Sandakozhi 2]]'' opposite [[Vishal (actor)|Vishal]], and ''[[Sarkar (2018 film)|Sarkar]]'' starring [[Vijay(actor)|Vijay]], directed by [[AR Murugadoss]].\n\nAs of 2019, she has signed on to appear in multiple projects such as the [[Malayalam]] film ''[[Marakkar: Arabikadalinte Simham]]'' directed by [[Priyadarshan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/kalyani-priyadarshan-confirms-working-keerthy-suresh-mohanlal-film-90276%3famp|title=Kalyani Priyadarshan confirms working with Keerthy Suresh for Mohanlal film|date=20 October 2018}}</ref> a yet to be titled [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film under the director Narendra Nath. She has a cameo appearance in the [[Nagarjuna]] starrer ''[[Manmadhudu 2]]'', which is directed by [[Rahul Ravindran]]. She is also set to make her [[Bollywood]] debut in ''[[Maidaan]]'' opposite [[Ajay Devgn]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"3\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"3\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 97%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Role(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Director(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Language(s)\n! s