ed Prince Charles (season 2)<ref name=\"CastComparisons\">{{cite web|url=https://the-crown-netflix.com/2017/12/11/the-crown-season-two-representation-vs-reality/|title=The Crown Season Two: Representation vs Reality|publisher=Netflix|date=11 December 2017|accessdate= 2 January 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Clancy Brown]] as [[Lyndon B. Johnson]], [[List of presidents of the United States|36th]] [[President of the United States]] (season 3)\n* [[Mark Lewis Jones]] as [[Edward Millward]] (season 3)\n* [[Tim McMullan]] as [[Robin Woods]] (season 3)\n* [[Harry Treadaway]] as [[Roddy Llewellyn]] (season 3)\n\n===Recurring===\n{{Div col|colwidth=35em}}<!-- List of NAMED characters recurring across multiple seasons. -->\n* Billy Jenkins as young Prince Charles (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 103 105 107 108 110 201 202 203 -->\n* Grace and Amelia Gilmour as young Princess Anne (seasons 1\u20132, uncredited)<ref>{{Cite book|last=Lacey|first=Robert|date=October 5, 2017|title=The Crown: The Inside History|url=https://www.blinkpublishing.co.uk/the-crown.html|location=London|publisher=[[Blink Publishing]]|page=354|isbn=9781911274988|author-link=}}</ref>\n* [[Clive Francis]] as [[Robert Gascoyne-Cecil, 5th Marquess of Salisbury|Lord Salisbury]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 102 103 104 105 107 109 201 203 206 -->\n* [[Pip Torrens]] as [[Alan Lascelles|Tommy Lascelles]] (seasons 1\u20132; guest season 3)<!-- 101 102 103 104 105 106 107 108 110 201 202 203 204 205 206 207 302 -->\n* [[Harry Hadden-Paton]] (seasons 1\u20132) and [[Charles Edwards (English actor)|Charles Edwards]] (season 3) as [[Martin Charteris, Baron Charteris of Amisfield|Martin Charteris]]<!-- 101 102 103 106 107 108 201 202 203 205 208 301 302 303 304 307 308 309 310 -->\n* [[Daniel Ings]] as [[Michael Parker (courtier)|Mike Parker]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 103 105 106 108 109 201 202 203 -->\n* Lizzy McInnerny as Margaret \"Bobo\" MacDonald (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 102 103 105 106 108 109 110 201 203 204 207 208-->\n* Michael Bertenshaw as the [[Piers Legh|Master of the Household]] (season 2; guest season 1)<!-- 101 201 208 -->\n* [[Patrick Ryecart]] as the [[Bernard Fitzalan-Howard, 16th Duke of Norfolk|Duke of Norfolk]] (seasons 1, 3; guest season 2)<!-- 101 103 105 203 306 310 -->\n* [[Will Keen]] (seasons 1\u20132) and [[David Rintoul]] (season 3) as [[Michael Adeane]]<ref name=\"RadioTimesCastPage2\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/on-demand/2019-11-04/meet-the-cast-of-the-crown-season-3/2/|title=Meet the cast of The Crown season 3|last=Bley Griffiths|first=Eleanor|magazine=[[Radio Times]]|date=4 November 2019|accessdate=10 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110050658/https://www.radiotimes.com/news/on-demand/2019-11-04/meet-the-cast-of-the-crown-season-3/2/|archive-date=November 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><!-- 101 106 107 108 109 110 201 202 203 204 205 206 207 208 210 301, 302, 303, 304, 305, 306, 307, 310 -->\n* [[James Laurenson]] as [[John Weir (physician)|Doctor Weir]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 102 104 207 210 -->\n* [[Mark Tandy (actor)|Mark Tandy]] as [[Cecil Beaton]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 101 110 203 204 206 210 -->\n* [[Rosalind Knight]] (season 1) and [[Sophie Leigh Stone]] (season 2) as [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]], Philip's mother \n* Andy Sanderson (season 1) and [[Michael Thomas (actor)|Michael Thomas]] (season 3) as [[Prince Henry, Duke of Gloucester]], Elizabeth's uncle<ref name=\"geeksofdoom\">{{cite web |url=http://www.geeksofdoom.com/2016/01/06/trailers-netflix-the-crown-the-get-down |title=Trailers for Netflix series 'The Crown,' and 'The Get Down' |website=Geeks of Doom |date=6 January 2016 |accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref> (seasons 1, 3)<!-- 101 102 103 105 107 108 301, 302, 304, 305, 307, 310-->\n* [[Michael Culkin]] as [[Rab Butler]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 102 104 109 201 203 207 -->\n* George Asprey as [[Walter Monckton]] (seasons 1\u20132)<!-- 102 103 104 201 203 206 -->\n* Verity Russell as young 